# Netlify routing.
#
# Weekly cache-bust: the SMS send includes /{week} in the URL (e.g.
# menu.havnclub.com/may10, menu.havnclub.com/welcome/may10). Each week has
# a unique URL, so messaging apps (iMessage, WhatsApp) regenerate the link
# preview instead of serving the previous week's cached image. Bump the
# prefix weekly alongside the menu deploy.
#
# Promo variants UNDER any weekly prefix — must come BEFORE the /:splat
# strip rule. Uses Netlify's :week placeholder so this works for any
# week slug (may17, may24, jun7, etc.) without needing weekly edits.
#
# Routes /{week}/welcome, /{week}/ws, /{week}/in to /index.html. The JS
# in index.html strips the /{week}/ prefix before detecting mode.
# Without these, /may17/ws would hit /:splat and rewrite to /ws, then
# Netlify wouldn't re-evaluate and would return 404.
/:week/welcome/*    /index.html  200
/:week/welcome      /index.html  200
/:week/ws/*         /index.html  200
/:week/ws           /index.html  200
/:week/db/*         /index.html  200
/:week/db           /index.html  200
/:week/in/*         /index.html  200
/:week/in           /index.html  200

# Strip the weekly prefix off everything else under /{week}/* — used for
# static asset cache-bust (e.g. /may17/menu-preview.png → /menu-preview.png).
/:week/*    /:splat 200

# Promo variants — same index.html, mode detected from window.location.pathname.
# Each path is routed via Make.com to its own customer cohort:
#   /welcome  → first-time customers (current $20-at-5 / $40-at-7 welcome offer)
#   /ws       → first + second timers ($25 with Wellness Shots + 7 meals)
#   /in       → inactive / win-back ($25 with Wellness Shots + 7 meals)
/welcome/*  /index.html 200
/welcome    /index.html 200
/ws/*       /index.html 200
/ws         /index.html 200
/db/*       /index.html 200
/db         /index.html 200
/in/*       /index.html 200
/in         /index.html 200

# Internal weekly performance review — unguessable path, not linked from anywhere
/may10-review  /may10-review.html  200

/*          /index.html 200
